public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        float number1 = 645.674356f;
        System.out.println("A float-sized decimal number is " + number1 + "\n");
        double number2 = 3229.0065389723451d;
        System.out.println("A double-sized decimal number is " + number2 + "\n");
    }
}

Output: 
A float-sized decimal number is 645.6744
A double-sized decimal number is 3229.006538972345
